text: Willy Kemp (28 December 1925 â€“ 18 October 2021) was a Luxembourgish professional road bicycle racer. He was born in Kopstal, Luxembourg. In 1949, he became national champion. Between 1948 and 1957, he rode every year the Tour de France (10 times in total) and won a stage in the 1955 Tour de France. Kemp died on 18 October 2021, at the age of 95. ==References== Category:1925 births Category:2021 deaths Category:Luxembourgian sportspeople Category:Cyclists
